[WPV1 (wild poliovirus) continues to circulate in Pakistan -- the report above confirms a case previously reported (see Poliomyelitis update (12): global (Afghanistan, Pakistan, Niger) 20190208.6306787 and see section [2] below reporting 2 additional cases in Punjab just confirmed). While there were no positive environmental samples reported from Afghanistan, it is too early to declare interruption of transmission of the WPV in Afghanistan.

As for cVDPVs, (circulating vaccine derived poliovirus), a new focus has been identified in Indonesia's Papua province, albeit according to the report above, the cVDPV1 identified in Indonesia is not related to the cVDPV1 identified in Papua New Guinea. As with WPV, it is too soon to declare interruption of transmission of the cVDPVs in Nigeria, Niger, Somalia, Mozambique, DR Congo, and Papua New Guinea.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

