Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The media report above mentions there have been 2 newly confirmed cases of wild poliovirus -- 1 in Lahore, Punjab, the other in Hangu, Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan. In the past few weeks there were reports of positive environmental samples in Punjab and Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, so the identification of active cases is not totally surprising. This will now bring the total number of WPV1 cases reported for 2019 to 5, with 4 of the 5 cases reported from Pakistan. - Mod.MPP]
